"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-nbcuniversals-paris-olympics-coverage-to-include-more-pop-culture-drama\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Published\\u00c2Jun 27, 2024, 02:48 AM  Updated\\u00c2Jun 27, 2024, 02:48 AM  From the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympics on July 26, U.S. television coverage of the games will include celebrities, social media influencers and generative artificial intelligence (AI), NBCUniversal said on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.019770634788669e-19, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999116718648748, \"rank\": 8.833593673691103e-05, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Comcast-owned media company, which paid $7.65 billion to renew its rights to air the Olympics in the U.S. through 2032, is seeking to modernize how it covers the world's largest sporting event.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stakes are high for NBC, which needs to win back viewers who are eschewing live television in favor of streaming services and watching clips online.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.8124111759848346, \"rank\": 0.22720506241133068, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pandemic delayed the Tokyo 2020 Summer Olympics and restricted attendance at the Beijing 2022 Winter games, which drew the smallest primetime viewership since NBCUniversal began airing the Olympics.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999116718648748, \"rank\": 8.833593673691103e-05, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans will be able to view personalized daily recaps of the Olympic competition created by generative AI and narrated by AI versions of people such as legendary sports commentator Al Michaels, Comcast CEO Brian Roberts said during a presentation in New York City.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999996819497, \"rank\": 3.180367853956697e-09, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999996819497, \"rank\": 3.180367853956697e-09, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1268, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.837069173559898e-38, \"text\": \"Al Michaels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 0.9999999999840838, \"rank\": 1.5823536664991642e-11, \"text\": \"Comcast\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1090005888538691e-27, \"text\": \"Brian Roberts\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999874626156, \"rank\": 1.253728497069017e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearly 7 million different variations of the recaps could be created over the course of the games, Roberts said.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In another sign of the times, NBC Sports anchors including Mike Tirico will share coverage duties with personalities like rapper Snoop Dogg and \\\"Call Her Daddy\\\" podcast host Alex Cooper in order to attract younger viewers.\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9978162640290666, \"rank\": 0.0021881551062195867, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mike Tirico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\"}, {\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\", \"score\": 0.8607573575018954, \"rank\": 0.16176470588237404, \"text\": \"Alex Cooper\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snoop Dogg will interview and tell the stories of Team USA athletes as well as their parents.\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1691, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.